        <h1 id="12_2024">RelBib is hosting the <i>Zeitschrift für junge Religionswissenschaft</i> (ZjR)</h1>
        <p class="rb-news-date">(December 2024)</p>
        <p>The <i>Zeitschrift für junge Religionswissenschaft</i> (ZjR) is an international open access journal that has been published by early-career scholars of religion (pre-doc) since 2006. Since 2024, it has been published in cooperation with the German Association for Study of Religion (<a href="https://www.dvrw.uni-hannover.de/de/" target="_blank">DVRW</a>). The ZjR is published twice a year and offers a platform for current and future scholars of the subject and their new, sometimes unorthodox, certainly exciting and forward-looking ideas, theories, methods and perspectives on the field of religion(s).</p>
		<p>The FID for the Study of Religion at Tübingen University Library has taken over the hosting of the ZjR and provides the editorial team with a new publication environment based on the Open Journal Systems (<a href="https://pkp.sfu.ca/software/ojs/" target="_blank">OJS by PKP</a>). Since December 2023, the ZjR has been available online with its new website at <a href="https://junge-religionswissenschaft.de"/a>. In September 2024, the first issue with eight articles was published, the editorial workflow of which was carried out entirely in the new publication environment.</p>
		<p>All articles are provided with a DOI and are indexed in RelBib to ensure that they can be cited and found in the long term:</p>
		<p><a href="https://relbib.de/Search/Results?lookfor=superior_ppn:514530790" target="_blank">The ZjR articles in RelBib </a></p>
    </li>
