        <h1 id="05_2022">National License for World Religion Database (WRD) now available!</h1>
        <p class="rb-news-date">(May 2022)</p>
        <p>For the new funding period (2022-2024), the FID Study of Religion has purchased free access to the World Religion Database at German universities, research institutes, and academic libraries. This national licence is funded by the German Research Foundation (DFG). </p>
        <p>The World Religion Database contains extensive demographic statistics on the respective religious affiliations in each country of the world. The data comes from surveys and polls and is supplemented by scientific estimates to enable comparisons and show developments. Data and estimates are provided for the period 1900 to 2050. The lists can be retrieved according to various criteria, e.g. by denomination or geography. This database is published and regularly updated by the Institute on Culture, Religion, and World Affairs (CURA), Boston University.</p>
        <p>Access to the national licence is being gradually activated for the participating institutions - please therefore check whether you already have access via your institution, otherwise we kindly ask for your patience. Alternatively, individuals with a permanent residence in Germany can also register for use at <a href="https://www.nationallizenzen.de" target="_blank">www.nationallizenzen.de</a>.</p>
        <p>If you have any questions concerning our FID licenses, please do not hesitate to contact the <a href="mailto:relbib@ub.uni-tuebingen.de">RelBib team</a>.</p>
    </li>

